  "\\label{def:group-hom}\nLet $(G, \\cdot)$ and $(H, \\ast)$ be groups in the sense of Definition~\\ref{def:group-classical}.\nA map $\\phi : G \\to H$ is a \\emph{group homomorphism} if\n\\[\n  \\phi(a \\cdot b) = \\phi(a) \\ast \\phi(b) \\quad \\text{for all } a, b \\in G.\n\\]\nIf $\\phi$ is also a bijection it is called an \\emph{isomorphism}, and we write $G \\cong H$.",
  :type :definition,
  :title "Group Homomorphism",
  :concepts [],
  :label "def:group-hom",
  :id "e087180c",
  :source-file "lie-groups.tex",
  :area "Lie Groups and Lie Algebras",
  :depends-on ["71746aac"],
  :created-at "2026-03-27"}
