  "\\label{def:subgroup}\nLet $G$ be a group (Definition~\\ref{def:group-classical}).\nA subset $H \\subseteq G$ is a \\emph{subgroup}, written $H \\leq G$, if it is closed under multiplication and inverses and contains the identity.\nIt is \\emph{normal}, written $H \\trianglelefteq G$, if $gHg^{-1} = H$ for all $g \\in G$.",
  :type :definition,
  :title "Subgroup and Normal Subgroup",
  :concepts [],
  :label "def:subgroup",
  :id "3d67b716",
