  "\\label{def:group-action}\nA \\emph{left action} of a group $G$ (Definition~\\ref{def:group-classical}) on a set $X$ is a map $G \\times X \\to X$, written $(g, x) \\mapsto g \\cdot x$, satisfying\n\\[\n  e \\cdot x = x \\quad \\text{and} \\quad g \\cdot (h \\cdot x) = (gh) \\cdot x \\quad \\text{for all } g,h \\in G,\\, x \\in X.\n\\]",
  :type :definition,
  :title "Group Action",
  :concepts [],
  :label "def:group-action",
