  "\\label{def:orbit-stabilizer}\nLet $G$ act on $X$ (Definition~\\ref{def:group-action}).\nFor $x \\in X$, the \\emph{orbit} and \\emph{stabilizer} of $x$ are\n\\[\n  G \\cdot x := \\{ g \\cdot x \\mid g \\in G \\}, \\qquad\n  G_x := \\{ g \\in G \\mid g \\cdot x = x \\}.\n\\]\nNote that $G_x \\leq G$ is a subgroup in the sense of Definition~\\ref{def:subgroup}.",
  :type :definition,
  :title "Orbit and Stabilizer",
  :concepts [],
  :label "def:orbit-stabilizer",
  :id "1641e614",
  :source-file "lie-groups.tex",
  :area "Lie Groups and Lie Algebras",
  :depends-on ["f7184fc4" "3d67b716"],
  :created-at "2026-03-27"}
 {:tags [],
  :proof-latex nil,
  :refs ["def:orbit-stabilizer" "def:subgroup" "def:quotient-group"],
  :latex
  "\\label{thm:orbit-stab}\nFor any $x \\in X$ with orbit and stabilizer as in Definition~\\ref{def:orbit-stabilizer},\n\\[\n  |G \\cdot x| = [G : G_x],\n\\]\nwhere $[G : G_x]$ is the index of the subgroup $G_x \\leq G$ (Definition~\\ref{def:subgroup}), equivalently the cardinality of the quotient $G/G_x$ (Definition~\\ref{def:quotient-group}).\nIn particular, if $G$ is finite then $|G| = |G \\cdot x| \\cdot |G_x|$.",
  :type :theorem,
  :title "Orbit-Stabilizer Theorem",
  :concepts [],
  :label "thm:orbit-stab",
  :id "28571139",
  :source-file "lie-groups.tex",
  :area "Lie Groups and Lie Algebras",
  :depends-on ["1641e614" "3d67b716" "4ceac839"],
