  "\\label{def:continuous-homeomorphism}\nLet $(X, \\mathcal{T}_X)$ and $(Y, \\mathcal{T}_Y)$ be topological spaces (Definition~\\ref{def:topological-space}).\nA map $f : X \\to Y$ is \\emph{continuous} if $f^{-1}(U) \\in \\mathcal{T}_X$ for every $U \\in \\mathcal{T}_Y$.\nIf $f$ is a continuous bijection with continuous inverse, it is a \\emph{homeomorphism}, and we write $X \\cong Y$.",
  :type :definition,
  :title "Continuous Map and Homeomorphism",
