  "\\label{def:compact}\nA topological space $X$ (Definition~\\ref{def:topological-space}) is \\emph{compact} if every open cover of $X$ has a finite subcover.\nA subset $A \\subseteq \\mathbb{R}^n$ is compact if and only if it is closed and bounded (Heine--Borel).",
  :type :definition,
  :title "Compactness",
