  "\\label{def:topological-manifold}\nA \\emph{topological $n$-manifold} is a Hausdorff, second-countable topological space $M$ (Definition~\\ref{def:topological-space}) such that every point $p \\in M$ has a neighbourhood homeomorphic (Definition~\\ref{def:continuous-homeomorphism}) to an open subset of $\\mathbb{R}^n$.",
  :type :definition,
  :title "Topological Manifold",
