  "\\label{def:smooth-manifold}\nA topological $n$-manifold $M$ (Definition~\\ref{def:topological-manifold}) is a \\emph{smooth manifold} if it is equipped with a maximal smooth atlas: a collection of charts $(U_\\alpha, \\varphi_\\alpha)$ covering $M$ such that all transition maps $\\varphi_\\beta \\circ \\varphi_\\alpha^{-1}$ are smooth.",
  :type :definition,
  :title "Smooth Manifold",
