  "\\label{def:smooth-map}\nA map $f : M \\to N$ between smooth manifolds (Definition~\\ref{def:smooth-manifold}) is \\emph{smooth} if its coordinate representations are smooth.\nIt is a \\emph{diffeomorphism} if it is a smooth bijection with smooth inverse; in particular a diffeomorphism is a homeomorphism (Definition~\\ref{def:continuous-homeomorphism}).",
