  "\\label{def:covering-space}\nA continuous map $p : \\widetilde{X} \\to X$ (Definition~\\ref{def:continuous-homeomorphism}) between topological spaces (Definition~\\ref{def:topological-space}) is a \\emph{covering map} if every point $x \\in X$ has an open neighbourhood $U$ such that $p^{-1}(U)$ is a disjoint union of open sets each mapped homeomorphically to $U$ by $p$.\nThe \\emph{universal cover} $\\widetilde{X}$ is the unique (up to isomorphism) simply connected (Definition~\\ref{def:simply-connected}) covering space of $X$.",
