  "\\label{thm:universal-cover}\nIf $G$ is a connected (Definition~\\ref{def:connected}) Lie group, its universal cover $\\widetilde{G}$ (Definition~\\ref{def:covering-space}) carries a unique Lie group structure such that the covering map $p : \\widetilde{G} \\to G$ is a Lie group homomorphism (Definition~\\ref{def:group-hom}). The kernel $\\ker p$ (Definition~\\ref{def:kernel-image}) is a discrete central subgroup (Definition~\\ref{def:subgroup}) of $\\widetilde{G}$.",
  :type :theorem,
  :title "Universal Cover of a Lie Group",
  :concepts [],
  :label "thm:universal-cover",
  :id "738e8542",
  :source-file "lie-groups.tex",
