  "\\label{def:representation}\nA \\emph{(linear) representation} of a group $G$ (Definition~\\ref{def:group-classical}) on a vector space $V$ over a field $k$ is a group homomorphism (Definition~\\ref{def:group-hom})\n\\[\n  \\rho : G \\to \\mathrm{GL}(V).\n\\]\nWe say $(V, \\rho)$ is a \\emph{$G$-representation}, or simply a \\emph{$G$-module}. The \\emph{dimension} of the representation is $\\dim V$.",
  :type :definition,
  :title "Representation",
  :concepts [],
  :label "def:representation",
  :id "ca6bd350",
  :source-file "lie-groups.tex",
  :area "Lie Groups and Lie Algebras",
  :depends-on ["71746aac" "e087180c"],
  :created-at "2026-03-27"}
 {:tags [],
