  "\\label{def:rv}\nA random variable $X$ is a measurable function from the sample space $\\Omega$ to $\\R$ \n\n$$ X : \\Omega \\to \\R $$ \n\nthat is, the inverse of any Borel Set in $\\R$ is $\\mathcal{F}$-measurable: \n$$ X^{-1} (A) = \\{\\omega : X(\\omega) \\in A \\} \\in \\mathcal{F} \\quad \\forall A \\in \\R $$",
  :type :definition,
