 {:tags [],
  :proof-latex
  "Let\n\n$$\nF : \\mathcal{C} \\to \\mathcal{D},\n\\qquad\nG : \\mathcal{D} \\to \\mathcal{E},\n\\qquad\nH : \\mathcal{E} \\to \\mathcal{F}.\n$$\n\nFor an object $X$,\n\n$$\nH \\circ (G \\circ F)(X)\n=\nH(G(F(X))).\n$$\n\nAlso\n\n$$\n(H \\circ G) \\circ F (X)\n=\nH(G(F(X))).\n$$\n\nThus the two functors agree on objects.\n\nFor a morphism $f : X \\to Y$,\n\n$$\nH \\circ (G \\circ F)(f)\n=\nH(G(F(f))).\n$$\n\nSimilarly,\n\n$$\n(H \\circ G) \\circ F (f)\n=\nH(G(F(f))).\n$$\n\nThus the functors agree on morphisms.",
  :refs ["def:functor-composition"],
  :latex
